---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h1
        class="to-primary dark:to-primary/80 mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-slate-900 bg-clip-text text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-transparent md:text-5xl dark:from-white"
      >
        How to Play
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
        A complete guide to Treachery — where alliances are secret and everyone
        has an agenda.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Overview</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Treachery is a social deduction game built on top of Magic: The
          Gathering, designed to work seamlessly with the Commander/EDH format.
          Think of it as a political thriller where everyone holds secrets —
          some players want to protect the Leader, others want them dead, and a
          few are playing their own hidden game entirely.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          There are four possible roles to receive: <strong>Leader</strong>, <strong
            >Guardian</strong
          >, <strong>Assassin</strong>, and <strong>Traitor</strong>. Each comes
          with its own win condition, creating a dynamic where nobody truly
          knows who their allies are until the cards are on the table.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">The Core Experience</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          If you've ever played party games like Werewolf, BANG!, or The
          Resistance, you'll feel right at home. The social dynamics here are
          completely different from a standard Magic game — alliances shift,
          promises get broken, and survival depends on reading your opponents
          correctly.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Deception is part of the game. You might claim to be a Guardian when
          you're actually an Assassin. You might feign suspicion of an ally to
          throw others off your trail. <strong
            >The only rule: trust no one.</strong
          >
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Best played with <strong>5-7 players</strong>, but works with 4 or 8+
          as well.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold">The Four Roles</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Your role is secret — except for the Leader, who must announce
        themselves at the start. Everything else is a matter of interpretation.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div
          class="rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500/10 to-amber-600/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div
              class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-amber-500"
            >
              <span class="text-2xl">👑</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Leader</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            The exposed target. Wins the game alongside any Guardians, but only
            if they survive to the end.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-xl border border-blue-500/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500/10 to-blue-600/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div
              class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-500"
            >
              <span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Guardian</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            The hidden protector. Shares the Leader's fate — victory if they
            live, defeat if they fall.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-xl border border-red-500/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-red-500/10 to-red-600/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div
              class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-red-500"
            >
              <span class="text-2xl">🗡️</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Assassin</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            The hunter. Victory comes the moment the Leader is eliminated from
            the game.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-xl border border-purple-500/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500/10 to-purple-600/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div
              class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-purple-500"
            >
              <span class="text-2xl">🎭</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Traitor</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            The opportunist. Must outlast everyone else — which means
            eliminating both Assassins and other Traitors before taking down the
            Leader.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Identity Cards Explained</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Your Identity is represented by a custom Magic card that sits in the
          command zone throughout the game. The card's subtype determines your
          role and win condition.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Most Identities have an <strong>Unveil ability</strong> — a one-time effect
          that triggers when you flip the card face-up. Using it changes the game
          dramatically, but there's a catch: everyone now knows who you are. Timing
          is everything.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          While Identities remain face-down, all players are technically
          opponents to each other — making early-game politics especially
          chaotic.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold">Setup by Player Count</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Choose your Identity deck based on how many people are playing. Shuffle,
        deal face-down, and let everyone peek at their card in secret. The
        Leader immediately reveals themselves and takes the first turn.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Players</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Leader</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Traitor</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Assassin</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Guardian</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">4</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">-</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">5</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">6</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">3</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">7</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">3</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">8</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">3</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">No Cards? No Problem</h2>
      <div class="rounded-xl bg-slate-100 p-6 dark:bg-slate-800/50">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          For a quick intro, you can represent roles with basic lands instead of
          printing Identity cards:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div
              class="mx-auto mb-2 flex h-20 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded border border-slate-300 bg-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-700"
            >
              <span class="text-xs font-bold">Plains</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400"
              >Leader</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <div
              class="mx-auto mb-2 flex h-20 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded border border-slate-300 bg-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-700"
            >
              <span class="text-xs font-bold">Island</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400"
              >Guardian</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <div
              class="mx-auto mb-2 flex h-20 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded border border-slate-300 bg-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-700"
            >
              <span class="text-xs font-bold">Mountain</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-red-600 dark:text-red-400"
              >Assassin</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <div
              class="mx-auto mb-2 flex h-20 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded border border-slate-300 bg-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-700"
            >
              <span class="text-xs font-bold">Swamp</span>
            </div>
            <span
              class="text-sm font-medium text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400"
              >Traitor</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Choosing Your Identities</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Identity cards come in different rarities that reflect their
          complexity, not their power. All cards are balanced — but some require
          more strategic thinking than others.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          <span
            class="mr-1 inline-flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-500/20 align-middle text-xs font-bold text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400"
            >◆</span
          >
          <strong class="text-purple-500">Special rarities</strong> are high-chaos,
          game-changing cards. Including or excluding them lets you tailor the experience
          to your group.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="p-4 text-center">
          <div
            class="mx-auto mb-3 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-bold">C</span>
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Common</span>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">Straightforward effects</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 text-center">
          <div
            class="mx-auto mb-3 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-green-500/20"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400"
              >U</span
            >
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Uncommon</span>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">Best for new players</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 text-center">
          <div
            class="mx-auto mb-3 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-blue-500/20"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400"
              >R</span
            >
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Rare</span>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">For experienced players</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 text-center">
          <div
            class="mx-auto mb-3 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-orange-500/20"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400"
              >M</span
            >
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Mythic</span>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">Expert level only</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-700/50 dark:bg-amber-900/20"
      >
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
          <strong>Getting started:</strong> Stick to uncommon Identities for your
          first few games. Once everyone understands the dynamics, you can introduce
          rarer cards for more complex strategies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Ready to Start?</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Browse all available Identity cards or dive into the full rulebook.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/oracle"
          class="bg-primary hover:bg-primary/90 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-6 py-3 font-medium text-white transition-colors"
        >
          Browse the Oracle
        </a>
        <a
          href="/rules"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-slate-200 px-6 py-3 font-medium text-slate-900 transition-colors hover:bg-slate-300 dark:bg-slate-700 dark:text-white dark:hover:bg-slate-600"
        >
          Read the Rules
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
